Wednesday's boys' cross country roundup: York Suburban sweeps Dallastown, York Catholic GameTimePA.com staff Posted: 10/01/2015 09:49:52 PM EDT Boys' cross country 
YORK SUBURBAN SWEEPS AT HOME >> York Suburban runners claimed the top four individual spots in a home sweep of Dallastown and York Catholic. 
Donovan Mears led the pack through the line at 17:36.28, narrowly edging teammate Peter Wagner (17:36.46), followed by Bryce Ohl (17:48.28) and Jarrett Raudensky (17:53.30). 
Dallastown's Patrick Jacobson interrupted the Trojan train, finishing fifth in 17:53.52. 3.1 miles at York Suburban 
York Suburban 16, Dallastown 45 York Suburban 15, York Catholic 50 Dallastown 18, York Catholic 45 
1. Donovan Mears, YS, 17:36.28. 2. Peter Wagner, YS, 17:36.46. 3. Bryce Ohl, YS, 17:48.28. 4. Jarrett Raudensky, YS, 17:53.30. 5. Patrick Jacobson, Dt, 17:53.52. 6. Quentin Schorr, YS, 18:14.41. 7.
